\subsection{the course}

%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%
\begin{frame}{What will we do?}
I will:
\begin{itemize}
\item give you all the slides (so write only what is not being displayed)
\item explain you the main principles of the \r \ language and some useful functions
\item provide you with short exercises to put concepts into practice
\item provide you with suggestions on how to learn more about \r \ on your own
\end{itemize}
\vfill
\pause
You will not:
\begin{itemize}
\item be fluent in the \r \ language after one week
\item be able to remember how to implement many of the things we will see
\end{itemize}
\pause
\vfill
You should:
\begin{itemize}
\item ``\emph{accept that you are gonna be frustrated, accept that you are gonna be bad at it for a while, but you have to keep going anyway\dots}'' (Wickham 2018, \url{https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Uxdf8evD6pQ})
\item ask any silly question that pops up in your creative minds
\item let me know immediately when you stop following
\end{itemize}
\end{frame}

